cleanup: Preemptively iterates through all stored keys and removes the ones which have expired.
prune:
To ensure entries fit within the specified memory prune the cache by removing the least
recently accessed entries.
pruning?: Returns true if the cache is currently being pruned.
increment: Increment an integer value in the cache.
decrement: Decrement an integer value in the cache.
synchronize:
Synchronize calls to the cache. This should be called wherever the underlying cache implementation
is not thread safe.
